{
  "stem": "22972.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Actually, in March, we went to say goodbye to my grandparents in Munich, and we were on a boat in-- on April 6th [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to come to America in 1938.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father was a very unusual man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In 1933, when we went to Denmark-- which I mentioned earlier-- with my Tante Greta, the great opera singer, we came back through Hamburg on the way home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Manhattan-- the SS Manhattan-- one of the two great ships of the United States steam line, was docked in dry dock in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my father talked his way onto the boat, and he picked out the cabin which we would deign to come to America on, because he wasn't going to come on a German ship.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was going to be on an American ship just as quick as he could, as soon as we got-- I mean, little did he think, in 1933, it would take my uncle in Cleveland to wait five whole years to send us that darn aff-- affidavit.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he picked out cabin number B23 and, sure enough, five years later, we came to America in cabin number B23, which was pretty amazing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We came-- we arrived in New York and my father, of course, being the Prussian officer, was the first in line at immigration.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And first, he pulled me up to show me the wonderful Statue of Liberty, and he was the first in line.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was the immigration officer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he looked at the papers and he said, Friedsam?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Are you related to Michael Friedsam?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father said, naturlich.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course I am.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father spoke English.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had lived in London for five years before the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And both my parents spoke English.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
